# Terraform state IS committed to this repo. This org-level config holds no
# secrets in state (verified: no tokens, no provider-sensitive attributes), and
# CI is the sole state writer. See README "State". Only backups/locals are
# ignored — never commit a state file that contains secrets.
*.tfstate.backup
*.tfstate.*.backup
.terraform/
.terraform.lock.hcl.bak
crash.log
crash.*.log

# Auto-loaded var files may carry secrets — keep them out of git.
# (terraform.tfvars itself IS committed: it's the declarative org config and
# holds no secrets. Auth comes from $GITHUB_TOKEN, never a var file.)
*.auto.tfvars
secret.tfvars
*.secret.tfvars
override.tf
override.tf.json
*_override.tf
*_override.tf.json

# Plan output (can leak values).
*.tfplan
plan.out
